=======================================================================================================================
Symmetric Encryption :-
1.Same Secret key is used for both encryption & decryption.
2.It is fast & used for large data.
Dis :-
1.Needs to be secure our key.

=======================================================================================================================
Types of Symmetric Encryption :-
=======================================================================================================================
1ï¸âƒ£DES (Data Encryption Standard) âŒ Obsolete :-

1.It is a weak encryption & key size is 56 bits(very small), Block size 8 bytes & slow as it uses brute-forced.
2.Do NOT use in real systems.
3.Only for legacy / interview knowledge.
4.DES input length must be multiple of 8 when decryption with padded cipher.
5.Will get javax.crypto.IllegalBlockSizeException if block size is not 8 bytes.

=======================================================================================================================
2ï¸âƒ£ 3DES (Triple DES) âš ï¸ Legacy :-

1.It works like Encrypt â†’ Decrypt â†’ Encrypt (DES Ã— 3).
2.Key Size is 112 or 168 bits & Block size 8 bytes.
3.Safer than DES but slow, deprecated now.
4.3DES input length must be multiple of 8 when decryption with padded cipher.
5.Will get javax.crypto.IllegalBlockSizeException if block size is not 8 bytes(64 bits) .
=======================================================================================================================
3ï¸âƒ£ AES (Advanced Encryption Standard) âœ… GOLD STANDARD :-

1.It is fast, key size is 128/192/256 bits & Block size is fixed 128 bits(16 bytes).
2.It is mainly used in HTTPS, JWT, Databases, Disk Encryption, etc.
Modes in AES->
1ï¸âƒ£ ECB (Electronic Codebook) âŒ NEVER USE :-
ECB leaks patterns and must never be used.
Cipher.getInstance("AES/ECB/PKCS5Padding"); // âŒ

2ï¸âƒ£ CBC (Cipher Block Chaining) âš ï¸ Legacy
CBC provides confidentiality but not authenticity.
Cipher.getInstance("AES/CBC/PKCS5Padding");

3ï¸âƒ£ CFB (Cipher Feedback)
âš ï¸ Rarely used today

4ï¸âƒ£ OFB (Output Feedback)
âš ï¸ Obsolete

5ï¸âƒ£ CTR (Counter Mode) âš ï¸ Fast but risky
âš ï¸ Use only with MAC
Cipher.getInstance("AES/CTR/NoPadding");

6ï¸âƒ£ GCM (Galois/Counter Mode) âœ… BEST PRACTICE
AES-GCM provides authenticated encryption and is the industry standard.
Cipher.getInstance("AES/GCM/NoPadding");

7ï¸âƒ£ CCM (Counter with CBC-MAC)
âš ï¸ Less common than GCM

8ï¸âƒ£ XTS (Disk Encryption)
âš ï¸ Specialized use only
