=======================================================================================================================
Asymmetric Encryption :-
Java supports asymmetric crypto mainly via JCA/JCE (java.security, javax.crypto).
1.Encryption is done by Public Key where as Decryption is done by Private Key.
2.It is fast & used for small data.
Public Key â†’ Shared with everyone.
Private Key â†’ Kept secret by the owner.
How it works:-
Encrypt with public key â†’ decrypt with private key.
Sign with private key â†’ verify with public key.
Why Asymmetric :-
Because it Solves key-sharing problem which we are facing in symmetric encryption
=======================================================================================================================
Types of Asymmetric Encryption :-
=======================================================================================================================
1ï¸âƒ£ RSA (Rivest, Shamir, and Adleman) :-

1.It is most widely used.
2.It use case is Key Exchange, Digital Signatures & Encrypting small data (keys, hashes).
3.Java supports KeyPairGenerator, Cipher & Signature.
4.Key Size 1024 (deprecated), 2048 (min required) & 3072/4096 (recommended).

=======================================================================================================================
2ï¸âƒ£ DSA (Digital Signature Algorithm) :-

1.It is only for signatures.
2.It use case is Digital Signature only there is no encryption.
3.Key Size 1024 (deprecated), 2048/3072 (recommended).

=======================================================================================================================
3ï¸âƒ£ Elliptic Curve Cryptography (ECC) :-

It is Modern, fast, and secure ğŸ”¥.

Two Types :-
1.ECDSA (Elliptic Curve Digital Signature Algorithm) :-
It use case is Digital Signature, JWT signing & TLS certificates.
Key Size (Curved-Based) is P-256, P-384 & P-521.

2.ECDH (Elliptic Curve Diffieâ€“Hellman) :-
It use case is Secure Key Exchange, TLS handshake & Generating shared secrets.

=======================================================================================================================
4ï¸âƒ£ Diffieâ€“Hellman (DH) :-

1.It is used for key-exchange only.
2.It use case is Secure Shared Key Generation & Predecessor of ECDH.
3.Key Size is 2048+ bits.
4.It is Slower than ECDH, used less today.

=======================================================================================================================
5ï¸âƒ£ EdDSA (Modern ECC â€“ very important ğŸš€)

1.It has two variants.
a>Ed25519
b>Ed448
2.It use case is Digital signatures, JWT, SSH & Modern TLS.
3.Java Supports 15+(native) or Bouncing Castle.
4.Benefits is Faster than RSA/ECDSA, Safer defaults & Deterministic signatures.

=======================================================================================================================
6ï¸âƒ£ ElGamal

1.Rarely used.
2.It use case is Encryption & Signatures.
3.Java Supports âŒ Not native, âœ… Bouncy Castle only.

=======================================================================================================================
7ï¸âƒ£ XDH (Key Agreement â€“ Modern)

1.It has two variants & Used with Ed curves.
a>X25519
b>X448
2.It use case is Digital signatures, & TLS 1.3.
3.Java Supports 11+.

